04/03/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- During a meeting Thursday (3 March), President Branko Crvenkovski and his Montenegrin counterpart, Filip Vujanovic, praised the level of bilateral relations and vowed to further extend co-operation, especially in the area of economics.
Crvenkovski added that preparations for opening a Macedonian consular office in Podgorica have entered the final stage.
For his part, Vujanovic stressed the importance of the transportation corridor through Kosovo, which he said has boosted trade considerably.
In other news, officials from Macedonia and Serbia agreed on Thursday that five new checkpoints should be opened along their common border.
They also pledged to continue dialogue in hopes of finding a solution to the issue of border demarcation between Macedonia and Kosovo.
(MIA, Makfax - 03/03/05)
